               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1421" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1421" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1421" type="surname" value="HOGARTH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1421" type="given" value="ANDREW"></interp>ANDREW HOGARTH</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">green-grocer, Charles-street, Stepney.</hi>) On the afternoon of 7th of April I was passing by a booth in Stepney fair with my child—I felt something at my pocket, turned, and saw the prisoner with my handkerchief in his hand, gathering it up, and making his way into the crowd—I took him by the arm—he dropped it, I picked it up—I had it just before to wipe the child's face with—I took the prisoner nearly to the station, and met a policeman.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1422" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1422" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1422" type="surname" value="STAMMER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1422" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY STAMMER</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable K</hi> 315.) At the station, I said to the prisoner, "Have you got anything about you?"—he said, "No"—I felt be<lb></lb>tween his shirt and his back, and pulled out this handkerchief—it is partly silk and partly cotton—he said he did not steal it, a boy gave it him outside—there was a mob of two or three hundred persons outside.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> The boy told me to mind it for him, and he would give me 1<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. when I came back. (The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
